group.description: Do what your group wants you to do.

attack_area.description: Go to a place and attack what you see.

stop.description: Stop moving and stay where you are.

build_base.description: Go to a position and build a base there.

logical_and.description: Fail on first failure. Only succeeds if all commands (executed one after another) succeed.

logical_or.description: Succeed on first success. Only fails if all commands (executed one after another) fail.

return_last.description: Execute all commands in sequence and fail or succeed depending on the return status of the last command.

ghost.description: Can't interact with the world, can only observe. Used in the multiplayer waiting-to-respawn screen.

character.description: The controller controls a character. This is the default controller in freeplay.

god.description: The controller isn't tied to a character. This is the default controller in sandbox.

editor.description: The Editor Controller near ultimate power to do almost anything in the game.

cutscene.description: The player can't interact with the world, and the camera pans around in a predefined manner.

spectator.description: Can't change anything in the world but can view anything.

none.description: Perform command even if someone attacks the unit.

by_enemy.description: Attack closer enemy entities with force.

by_anything.description: Attack closer enemy entities, including entities "built" by player (belts, inserters, chests).

no_input_fluid.description: Used by boilers, fluid turrets and fluid energy sources: Boiler has no fluid to work with.

low_input_fluid.description: Used by boilers and fluid turrets: Boiler still has some fluid but is about to run out.

full_output.description: Used by crafting machines, boilers, burner energy sources and reactors: Reactor/burner has full burnt result inventory, boiler has full output fluidbox.

missing_required_fluid.description: Used by mining drills when the mining fluid is missing.

waiting_for_space_in_destination.description: Used by inserters and mining drills.

disabled.description: Used by constant combinators: Combinator is turned off via switch in GUI.

path_lost.description: Had path and lost it -- must stop.

no_path.description: Has no path and is stopped.

manual_control_stop.description: Switched to manual control and has to stop.

manual_control.description: Can move if user explicitly sits in and rides the train.
